01:06:11.370 --> 01:06:14.590
And the initiative is quite
big because we have a lot

01:06:14.590 --> 01:06:20.740
of research groups involved now
in this research infrastructure.

01:06:20.740 --> 01:06:24.870
Monique is playing the-- well,
this, the concept more or less

01:06:24.870 --> 01:06:26.790
of research infrastructure
in Europe.

01:06:26.790 --> 01:06:31.450
I will try to explain what
this project is doing actually.

01:06:31.450 --> 01:06:38.620
Because the main activities of
the project providing services

01:06:38.620 --> 01:06:40.670
as a research infrastructure.

01:06:40.670 --> 01:06:42.990
And I will show you the services.

01:06:42.990 --> 01:06:50.240
Then the idea underneath the
proposal of IPERION CH was to try

01:06:50.240 --> 01:06:54.520
to structure something
more long term, let's say,

01:06:54.520 --> 01:06:59.290
because as you may know, projects
are short term by nature and also

01:06:59.290 --> 01:07:03.860
in this case, we have
initiatives that can last three

01:07:03.860 --> 01:07:07.020
to five years, no more than that.

01:07:07.020 --> 01:07:09.760
So the idea was to try to start

01:07:09.760 --> 01:07:14.350
to kick off a permanent
research infrastructure dealing

01:07:14.350 --> 01:07:17.100
with cultural heritage in Europe,

01:07:17.100 --> 01:07:23.970
thus trying to help the
scientific community using it.

01:07:23.970 --> 01:07:28.930
And this started considering
conservation or restoration,

01:07:28.930 --> 01:07:32.300
so strictly speaking cultural
heritage issues in Europe.

01:07:32.300 --> 01:07:36.290
But very soon we realize
that the horizon

01:07:36.290 --> 01:07:39.910
of this should have
been more inclusive.

01:07:39.910 --> 01:07:42.620
And so we finally decided to apply

01:07:42.620 --> 01:07:45.560
for a research infrastructure
covering the needs

01:07:45.560 --> 01:07:51.920
of the wider community of
heritage science, whatever it is.

01:07:51.920 --> 01:07:55.840
By the way, the main activities
of an integrating project,

01:07:55.840 --> 01:07:59.800
integrating activity
are of three natures.

01:07:59.800 --> 01:08:05.260
The first is providing services and
we call that transnational access.

01:08:05.260 --> 01:08:09.620
So the infrastructure is
providing services to research.

01:08:09.620 --> 01:08:14.000
The second activity is
upgrading these services

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:19.380
by doing joint research altogether.

01:08:19.380 --> 01:08:24.990
The third, but not the least
important activity is insuring a

01:08:24.990 --> 01:08:30.300
continuous of networking between
the European facilities providing

01:08:30.300 --> 01:08:31.600
the services.

01:08:31.600 --> 01:08:34.770
This is very important
because under the networking,

01:08:34.770 --> 01:08:37.030
you do a lot of things.

01:08:37.030 --> 01:08:39.240
You do the policies
of the infrastructure.

01:08:39.240 --> 01:08:40.610
You do the training.

01:08:40.610 --> 01:08:41.910
You do a lot.

01:08:41.910 --> 01:08:43.780
You do-- you organize event,

01:08:43.780 --> 01:08:46.190
international events,
European events.

01:08:46.190 --> 01:08:48.290
So the budget is limited
but the activity

01:08:48.290 --> 01:08:50.130
of networking is very important

01:08:50.130 --> 01:08:54.070
because it covers the
assistance that the future needs.

01:08:54.070 --> 01:08:58.990
About the services, the IPERION CH
infrastructure is providing three

01:08:58.990 --> 01:09:02.480
kind of services to research.

01:09:02.480 --> 01:09:06.330
The first is having
mobile instruments going

01:09:06.330 --> 01:09:11.890
where the artworks are and
having analytics of diagnostics

01:09:11.890 --> 01:09:15.880
of several impossible kinds
of physical, chemical.

01:09:15.880 --> 01:09:21.290
And this is called mobile
laboratory, so MOLAB.

01:09:21.290 --> 01:09:29.650
Then we provide services linked to
access to non-mobile laboratories.

01:09:29.650 --> 01:09:31.500
In the case of IPERION CH,

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:36.810
we only covers access
to landscape facilities.

01:09:36.810 --> 01:09:41.950
It's a [inaudible] room and two
accelerator in the mutual source.

01:09:41.950 --> 01:09:47.950
It is specialized in cultural
heritage applications.

01:09:47.950 --> 01:09:52.870
Then we provide access to archives.

01:09:52.870 --> 01:09:55.500
I use to call them
nondigital archives.

01:09:55.500 --> 01:09:58.000
But actually archives are archives

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:00.040
and they are nondigital
by definition.

01:10:00.040 --> 01:10:03.820
We are immersed in this digital
world, so we need to specify

01:10:03.820 --> 01:10:05.530
that these archives are nondigital.

01:10:05.530 --> 01:10:11.860
Archives where scientific documents
are including actually pieces

01:10:11.860 --> 01:10:16.230
of artworks, if you consider
cross-sections for instance

01:10:16.230 --> 01:10:21.710
or you can have samples
of pigments, samples of--

01:10:21.710 --> 01:10:27.210
so real physical object, as well
as non-digitized documentation.

01:10:27.210 --> 01:10:33.540
So currently, we are also
providing travel and accommodation

01:10:33.540 --> 01:10:37.300
for researchers who apply
for going to archives.

01:10:37.300 --> 01:10:45.890
In IPERION, we realized very
keen international interest

01:10:45.890 --> 01:10:51.340
in the initiative and that
is what produced our proposal

01:10:51.340 --> 01:10:56.970
as European infrastructure
with global scope.

