01:13:59.680 --> 01:14:05.630
What we will need to do
is two difficult things,

01:14:05.630 --> 01:14:08.210
but we need to do them both.

01:14:08.210 --> 01:14:11.300
Otherwise, the infrastructure
will not work.

01:14:11.300 --> 01:14:14.360
We will meet to define
a common approach

01:14:14.360 --> 01:14:18.400
to diagnostic methodologies,
analytics.

01:14:18.400 --> 01:14:21.320
Otherwise, we will not
have consistent data.

01:14:21.320 --> 01:14:23.290
And so we will not help research.

01:14:23.290 --> 01:14:25.950
We will continue supporting
the fragmentation

01:14:25.950 --> 01:14:28.160
of research in cultural heritage.

01:14:28.160 --> 01:14:31.660
So we first need to
establish a common approach.

01:14:31.660 --> 01:14:36.760 position:56%
So first in the creation of
practices, best practices in methods

01:14:36.760 --> 01:14:39.970
but also in the use of this data.

01:14:39.970 --> 01:14:45.130 position:56%
So we need to define a common data
infrastructure for heritage science.

01:14:45.130 --> 01:14:51.030
I don't know what of these two
things to do is the most difficult.

01:14:51.030 --> 01:14:54.150
But I only know that
we need to do both,

01:14:54.150 --> 01:15:00.300
because my motto is not digital
common data, no infrastructure

01:15:00.300 --> 01:15:05.890
at all due to the complexity
of the scientific landscape

01:15:05.890 --> 01:15:10.900
of institutions involve,
multidisciplinary and all things.

01:15:10.900 --> 01:15:15.350
We actually will need
common platform.

01:15:15.350 --> 01:15:19.640
We will need to the
common data infrastructure.

01:15:19.640 --> 01:15:22.670
Otherwise our languages--
we like [inaudible].

01:15:22.670 --> 01:15:26.940
Everybody will speak their own
languages and we will never to get

01:15:26.940 --> 01:15:30.530
